gomodel:SYNGO_2163  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Postsynaptic SNAP-47 KD Impairs LTP without Altering Basal Synaptic Transmission or Constitutive Recycling\"\nFig.6: \"SNARE-Dependent Interaction Is Required for SNAP-47's Role in LTP\"\n\nLiteral: \"These findings suggest that SNAP-47 specifically participates in the fusion machinery that is responsible for AMPAR exocytosis during LTP.\". Experimental description: - Dissociated cultures: \"Dissociated hippocampal cultures were prepared from newborn C57BL/6 mice\"\n- Slice recordings: \"CD1 (Charles River) mice (8-12 g) were prepared for stereotactic injection using standard procedures approved...\"\n- Species of the overexpressed protein is not stated in the manuscript.\n- Annotation to mouse species is made based on the shRNA experiments in mouse neurons." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2163" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

